If Americans want to change the Constitution, there is a process to amend it. But I cannot support creating any laws that infringe on our Constitutional rights.

When I was sworn in to the U.S. House of Representatives, I took an oath to uphold the Constitution and that includes the 2nd Amendment. Red flag laws would give one judge the ability to take away someone’s Constitutional right without due process.

The Certified Community Behavioral Health Clinic program helps people get the mental health treatment they need, instead of locking up people who have a mental health issue and substance use disorder.
Reforming 42 CFR Part 2 will help physicians treat substance abuse disorders and mental health issues like a regular medical condition, without the stigma that comes with along with it.
I’m currently working on 2 pieces of legislation, carried over from last Congress, that will address mental health laws.

But changing our Constitutional rights isn’t an option. As President Trump stated today, we need to reform our mental health laws & find real, bipartisan solutions that will actually fix the problem we are facing.
